\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki was fast asleep, her breathing steady as she sprawled on the iron-framed bed. The events of the previous day had left her exhausted, and she had fallen into a deep, dreamless sleep. The cabin was quiet, the only sound the faint rustling of leaves outside the window.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But then, a knock broke the silence.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 It was soft at first, almost tentative\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a single tap on the window. Haruki stirred slightly, her brow furrowing, but she didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t wake. A moment later, the knock came again, louder this time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki groaned, pulling the pillow over her face. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Go away,\u8221\'94 she mumbled, her voice muffled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The knocking persisted, growing more insistent. Tap. Tap. Tap.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki sat up suddenly, her hair a mess and her eyes bleary with sleep. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What is it?\u8221\'94 she snapped, her voice tinged with annoyance. She glared at the window, but the curtains were drawn, and she couldn\u8217\'92t see who\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or what\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 was outside.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 With a sigh, she threw off the covers and swung her legs over the side of the bed. Her feet hit the cool wooden floor, and she shuffled toward the door, rubbing her eyes. She unlocked it and pulled it open, squinting against the early morning light.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Standing on the doorstep was a figure she hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t expected to see.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 It was Sakura, standing on the doorstep with a bright smile. Behind her, the boys from the motorcycle gang were gathered, chatting and laughing. Nagano was among them, his guitar slung over his shoulder. When he saw Haruki open the door, he waved enthusiastically.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Morning, Haruki-chan!\u8221\'94 he called, his grin wide and carefree.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki blinked, still groggy from sleep. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What\u8230\'85 what are you all doing here?\u8221\'94 she asked, her voice tinged with confusion.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura stepped forward, her hands clasped behind her back. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We thought you lived somewhere close by, so we decided to visit,\u8221\'94 she explained. \u8220\'93Or, more accurately, Nagano-kun took quite a liking to you and decided to invite you to spend Saturday with us.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki stared at her, trying to process what she was hearing. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Wait, what?\u8221\'94 she said, her voice slow and disbelieving. Maybe it was the grogginess, but this felt like something out of a dream.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano stepped forward, his hands in his pockets. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well, you\u8217\'92re new here, right?\u8221\'94 he said, his tone casual but kind. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s important to have friends you can depend on. And honestly, you are rebellious and impulsive, I think you\u8217\'92ll fit with us.\u8221\'94 He grinned, clearly teasing her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki chuckled, taking it as a compliment. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks, I think,\u8221\'94 she said, her lips curling into a small smile.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura glanced past Haruki into the cabin, her expression curious. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93By the way, does your grandfather mind if you come with us? We heard you live with your grandparents. We don\u8217\'92t want to get you in trouble.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki froze for a moment, her mind racing. She had completely forgotten about the lie she had told about living with her grandfather. Thinking quickly, she turned her head slightly and called into the empty cabin, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Grandpa, is it okay if I go out with my friends? I\u8217\'92ll be back before nightfall!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She paused for a moment, as if listening to a response, then turned back to Sakura with a sheepish smile. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He says it\u8217\'92s fine, as long as I\u8217\'92m back before dark.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano, leaning against his motorcycle with his usual careless grin, chimed in. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Maybe you can just sneak out, Haruki. Your old man wouldn\u8217\'92t know.\u8221\'94 He winked, clearly teasing her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura shot him a disapproving look, her hands on her hips. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re horrible! Haruki could get in trouble!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano shrugged, unfazed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I sneak out all the time. My old man doesn\u8217\'92t care. He\u8217\'92s too busy with work to notice, anyway.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura rolled her eyes. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You definitely don\u8217\'92t know what it\u8217\'92s like to be a girl, Nagano. We can\u8217\'92t just do whatever we want. People talk, and it\u8217\'92s always us who get blamed.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano raised an eyebrow, his grin fading slightly. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, I guess you\u8217\'92re right. It\u8217\'92s not fair, but that\u8217\'92s just how it is, huh?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Alright then,\u8221\'94 she said, turning back to Haruki. \u8220\'93Go get ready. We\u8217\'92ll wait by the road at our usual spot.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki nodded and closed the door, leaning against it for a moment as she let out a quiet sigh of relief. That had been close. She hurried to the bedroom.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki opened the wardrobe in her bedroom, discovering that the clothes there all looked vintage. Well, they\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 were}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~vintage\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 or rather, they were the height of fashion in this time. But to her, they looked old-fashioned and unfamiliar. Haruki was used to her baggy hoodie, skinny jeans, and sneakers, but it seemed that style of fashion hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t made its way to 1961 yet. With a sigh, she pulled out a plain polo shirt, a cardigan, and one of the skirts that seemed to dominate the wardrobe. She slipped them on, feeling oddly out of place in her own skin.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Standing in front of the mirror, she paused. The reflection staring back at her looked\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85 different. The polo shirt and skirt gave her a polished, almost prim appearance, and the cardigan softened her edges in a way that felt strangely comforting. But what struck her most was how much she resembled her mother. It shouldn\u8217\'92t have surprised her\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Honoka probably dressed the same way at this age\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but the realization still caught her off guard. For a moment, she felt a pang of something she couldn\u8217\'92t quite name. Longing? Nostalgia? Or maybe just the bittersweet ache of seeing herself in someone she thought she knew so little about.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Shaking off the thought, Haruki grabbed her sketchbook and tucked it under her arm. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know where they were going, but she wasn\u8217\'92t about to leave without it. Taking a deep breath, she walked out the door and joined her friends.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The group was waiting by the road, their motorcycles gleaming in the morning sun. Nagano was leaning against his bike, strumming his guitar absently, while Sakura chatted with the other boys. When Haruki approached, Sakura turned and smiled.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93There you are! You look nice,\u8221\'94 she said, her tone warm and genuine.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki glanced down at her outfit, feeling self-conscious. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks. I guess this is what everyone wears here, huh?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano looked up from his guitar, his eyes scanning her with a playful grin. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, but you make it look cool. Not everyone can pull off the \u8216\'91serious student\u8217\'92 look.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki rolled her eyes, but she couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help smiling. \u8220\'93Thanks, I think.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura laughed, linking her arm with Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s. \u8220\'93Don\u8217\'92t mind him. He thinks he\u8217\'92s funny, but we all know better.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano feigned offense, clutching his chest dramatically. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ouch, Sakura. You wound me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The group erupted into laughter, and Haruki felt a flicker of warmth in her chest. It was strange, being here with these people who felt so familiar yet so different from the parents she knew. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, where are we going?\u8221\'94 Haruki asked, glancing around at the group.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano slung his guitar over his shoulder and hopped onto his motorcycle. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s a surprise. But trust me, you\u8217\'92re gonna love it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Sakura nudged Haruki gently. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Don\u8217\'92t worry, we\u8217\'92ll take care of you. Just hold on tight, okay?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki nodded, though a small knot of nervousness tightened in her stomach. She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d never ridden a motorcycle before, and the idea of speeding through the countryside with Nagano at the helm was equal parts thrilling and terrifying.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As the engines roared to life, Haruki climbed onto the back of Nagano\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s bike. The wind tugged at her hair as they sped down the road, the world blurring into a kaleidoscope of green fields and blue sky. For a moment, she forgot about the lies, the secrets, and the weight of her situation. She was just Haruki, a girl on an adventure with her friends, and for now, that was enough.}
